          "body": "The prologue's climax (1:16-18) names how the believer participates in this manifested fullness. *From His fullness we have all received, and grace upon grace* (1:16) — wave after wave of grace, continuous replenishment. Verse 17 names the covenantal advance: the Law was *given* through Moses (a true gift), but grace and truth *came into being* (*egeneto* again) through Jesus Christ. Not contradiction but fulfillment — Sinai was real, but Sinai was preparation. Verse 18 closes the prologue with the chapter's most exalted Christology: no one has ever seen God, but the only-begotten God (*monogenēs theos* — the better-attested reading) who is in the bosom of the Father, He has *exegeted* (*exēgēsato*) Him. Jesus is the exegesis of the invisible God."
